1.01	Defence_Food_Research_Laboratory	Defence Food Research Laboratory	The Defence Food Research Laboratory is an Indian defense laboratory of the Defence Research &amp; Development Organization (DRDO). Located in Mysore, Karnataka, it conducts research and development of technologies and products in the area of Food Science and Technology to cater the varied food challenges for the Indian Armed Forces. DFRL is organized under the Life Sciences Directorate of DRDO. The present director of DFRL is Dr. A.S. Bawa.	
